=head1 DESCRIPTION

A summary of information about an internet event in Amazon CloudWatch
Internet Monitor. Internet events are issues that cause performance
degradation or availability problems for impacted Amazon Web Services
client locations. Internet Monitor displays information about recent
global health events, called internet events, on a global outages map
that is available to all Amazon Web Services customers.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 B<REQUIRED> ClientLocation => L<Paws::InternetMonitor::ClientLocation>

The impacted location, such as a city, that Amazon Web Services clients
access application resources from.


=head2 EndedAt => Str

The time when an internet event ended. If the event hasn't ended yet,
this value is empty.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> EventArn => Str

The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the internet event.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> EventId => Str

The internally-generated identifier of an internet event.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> EventStatus => Str

The status of an internet event.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> EventType => Str

The type of network impairment.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> StartedAt => Str

The time when an internet event started.



